#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code har bar ko rectangle ki minimum height maan kar uska maximum possible area nikalta hai.

1. Har index ke liye previous smaller element ka index nikaala gaya hai.
   Matlab left me pehla chhota bar kahan hai.
2. Har index ke liye next smaller element ka index bhi nikaala gaya hai.
   Matlab right me pehla chhota bar kahan hai.
3. Ab current bar height ke liye rectangle ki width hogi:
   ns[i] - ps[i] - 1
4. Rectangle area:
   height[i] * width
5. Har bar ke liye area calculate karke maximum area store kar lete hain.

Main idea:
Agar kisi bar ko rectangle ki height maana jaye,
to rectangle left aur right me tab tak extend karega jab tak smaller bar na mil jaaye.

Important:
- previous smaller nahi mile to -1
- next smaller nahi mile to n
Ye boundary handling width nikalne ke liye zaroori hai.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

import java.util.Deque;
import java.util.ArrayDeque;

class Solution {

    public int[] previousSmaller(int[] heights){
        int n = heights.length;
        ArrayDeque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int[] ans = new int[n];

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && heights[stack.peek()] >= heights[i]){
                stack.pop();
            }

            if(stack.isEmpty()){
                ans[i] = -1;
            }
            else{
                ans[i] = stack.peek();
            }
            stack.push(i);
        }
        return ans;
    }
    public int[] nextSmaller(int[] heights){
        int n = heights.length;
        ArrayDeque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int[] ans = new int[n];

        for(int i=n-1; i>=0; i--){
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && heights[stack.peek()] >= heights[i]){
                stack.pop();
            }

            if(stack.isEmpty()){
                ans[i] = n;
            }
            else{
                ans[i] = stack.peek();
            }
            stack.push(i);
        }
        return ans;
    }

    public int largestRectangleArea(int[] heights) {
        int n = heights.length;
        int[] ps = previousSmaller(heights);
        int[] ns = nextSmaller(heights);
        int maxVal = 0;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            int curr = (ns[i] - ps[i] - 1) * heights[i];
            maxVal = Math.max(maxVal, curr);
        }
        return maxVal;

    }
}
